.TH GIT-FS 1
.SH NAME
git-fs \- mount a git repository as a filesystem

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-fs
[
.B \-af
]
[
.B \-m
.I mtpt
]
.br
.B git-fs
.B \-u
[
.I mtpt
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B Git-fs
mounts a git repository as a read-only filesystem.
Branches, tags, and commits are exposed as directories.
The repository is found by walking up from the working directory;
the default mountpoint is
.IR .git/fs/ .

.PP
New commits, branch updates, and tag updates in the underlying
repository are reflected on the next access.
Detection uses
.BR inotify (7),
not polling.

.PP
The top level contains the following entries:

.TP
.I HEAD/
The current commit.

.TP
.I branches/heads/
Local branches.
Each branch is a directory named after the ref.

.TP
.I branches/remotes/
Remote-tracking branches, grouped one directory per remote.

.TP
.I tags/
Tags.
Both lightweight and annotated tags are exposed as commit directories.

.TP
.I objects/
Every commit in the repository, named by full SHA.

.PP
Each ref or commit is the same hierarchy:

.TP
.I tree/
A directory containing the files at this revision.
The mtime of each entry is the commit date.

.TP
.I hash
The commit id.

.TP
.I msg
The full commit message.

.TP
.I parent/
The parent commit, as the same hierarchy.
For a merge commit, only the first parent is exposed.

.PP
Trees are presented as directory listings and blobs as files.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-m " mtpt"
Mount on
.IR mtpt .
The default is
.IR .git/fs/ .

.TP
\fB\-u\fR [\fImtpt\fR]
Unmount.
With no argument, unmounts
.I .git/fs/
of the repository in the current directory.

.TP
.B \-a
Allow other users to access the mount.
Requires
.B user_allow_other
in
.BR fuse.conf (5).

.TP
.B \-f
Run in the foreground.

.TP
.B \-V
Print the version and exit.

.TP
.B \-h
Print a usage summary and exit.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I .git/
The git repository being served.

.TP
.I .git/HEAD
The reference followed by
.IR .git/fs/HEAD/ .

.TP
.IR .git/refs/ ", " .git/packed-refs
Watched for changes; rebuilt listings are pushed to the kernel via
.BR fuse_lowlevel_notify_inval_entry (3).

.SH AUTHOR
Fernando González
.MT fernando.gonzalez@suse.com
.ME .

.SH "REPORTING BUGS"
Report bugs at
.UR https://github.com/fgyanz/git-fs/issues
.UE .

.SH BUGS
.PP
Branch names containing a slash (e.g.\&
.IR feature/foo )
are not exposed.

.PP
.BR readlink (2)
is not implemented.
Symbolic links recorded in a tree are reported as regular files
containing the link target.

.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IR fuse (8),
.IR git (1),
.IR inotify (7),
.IR mount.fuse3 (8)
